post_text:
NEW ATTEDANCE PROTOCOL

Hello JMPS Students! Starting on Monday, August 24th, teachers will be checking non-live class attendance with a question each day in the Classwork Tab entitled: ATTENDANCE- CLASS NAME- DATE (example: ATTENDANCE-ENGLISH 9- 8/24/20) This will be how all teachers will be checking that you are attending their non-live classes every day. All students must answer this question for their NON-LIVE classes Monday-Friday by 11:59 pm for each day. You must show up for your LIVE classes, and that counts as your attendance for those classes. This last week there has been some confusion about how attendance is being checked so we will be having a uniform approach moving forward. Please let your teachers know if you have questions!

ùêîùê©ùêùùêöùê≠ùêû ùê´ùêûùê†ùêöùê´ùêùùê¢ùêßùê† ùêûùê±ùê≠ùê´ùêöùêúùêÆùê´ùê´ùê¢ùêúùêÆùê•ùêöùê´ ùêöùêúùê≠ùê¢ùêØùê¢ùê≠ùê¢ùêûùê¨

Hello Patriot Fam,

As of right now the CAA has decided to postpone the Fall sports season. Therefore, James Madison Prep has no choice but to comply with the league and postpone all of our Fall practices and extracurricular activities.

The leagues intention is to begin practices in September and to have games start in October. The goal for the league and our school in general is to wait for the metrics to decrease within the state of Arizona. Once those numbers have steadily decreased for a number of weeks, the league will have another board meeting and decide whether they believe it is safe to start a Fall sports season. Your coaches will be in contact with you soon.

For quicker information from your coaches be sure to download the ‚ÄúRemind app‚Äù on your smart devices, as well as the school app, for updates on practices, start times and other important school/EC information.

Any other questions regarding extracurricular activities, please contact Coach Aljuwani: aaljuwani@madisonprep.org.

#JMPSaz #PatriotsPride

post_text:
Signature Packet Signing Clarification

We have had several questions about signing the Signature Packet online- please read the following for order of steps. If you have questions please email Mrs. Curtis at rcurtis@madisonprep.org: 1- One of the parents fills out the paperwork (make sure to include student name and email at the beginning of the process) 2- Parents and student review (make sure there are no misspellings, incorrect info, etc.) 3- Parent signs- clicks finish 4- Student locates latest email from DocuSign 5- Student signs- clicks finish Then it is submitted automatically to the school and parent https://www.docusign.net/Member/PowerFormSigning.aspx?PowerFormId=3d4c0e07-23a4-49a3-a1ad-d62f36167bd7&env=na1&acct=9136cdaa-cad4-4e44-b340-5f639b2bef25&v=2

post_text: Jake Eggen was offered the opportunity to play baseball at Knox College, which is a NCAA Division III school. Knox College is located in Galesburg, Illinois (a few hours southwest of Chicago). Jake plans on studying Environmental Science and possibly double majoring. Jake hopes to get involved in a few advocacy groups including: Students for Sustainability, The Good Athlete Project, and the Food Recovery Network. Jake officially signed the paperwork to secure his spot at Knox College on May 1st and we could not be prouder of him and are so excited to see what he does over the next four years. Congratulations, Jake!! You have truly earned this amazing opportunity!

post_text:
Official Directors‚Äô Statement 22 April 2020
JMPS Online School Success
A GREAT BIG SHOUT OUT and CONGRATULATIONS to JMPS students and staff for doing such a great job in these difficult times. We are hearing and reading about online student participation around the state and the country of less than 50% in the case of some schools, and we are really proud of our community for putting in such a strong effort. Over 90% of JMPS students have checked in and started their classes, and well over 80% are completing their assignments weekly. Thanks to EVERYBODY (students, parents, and teachers) for being such great JMPS Patriots and Living the Code. Stay Safe!
text:
Official Directors‚Äô Statement 22 April 2020
JMPS Online School Success
A GREAT BIG SHOUT OUT and CONGRATULATIONS to JMPS students and staff for doing such a great job in these difficult times. We are hearing and reading about online student participation around the state and the country of less than 50% in the case of some schools, and we are really proud of our community for putting in such a strong effort. Over 90% of JMPS students have checked in and started their classes, and well over 80% are completing their assignments weekly. Thanks to EVERYBODY (students, parents, and teachers) for being such great JMPS Patriots and Living the Code. Stay Safe!

post_text:
Hello Patriot Families,

If your child is interested in participating in any of our Fall extracurricular activities, please contact Coach Aljuwani (aaljuwani@madisonprep.org) with your students name and which sport he or she would like to play. Their options are varsity football, varsity volleyball, JV volleyball, Sparx, and drumline. Fees paid before June 30th will be discounted to $260 for football and volleyball, and $200 for Sparx and Drum Line. If paid after June 30th, the fees for varsity football, varsity volleyball and JV volleyball are $285. The fees for Sparx and Drum Line are $225. If you have any questions regarding fee's or making payments, please contact Mrs. Grant (sgrant@madisonprep.org). Any questions regarding sports, please contact Coach Aljuwani. Thank you! Go Patriots!

post_text: Join us for the JMPS Holiday Festival on Friday, December 13th starting at 6 p.m. Stroll through the classrooms as the students display their creativity during our annual homeroom decorating competition and enjoy holiday performances from several of our musical groups. The Choir will be caroling around the campus from 6 p.m. to 6:45 p.m., the Ukulele Ensemble will perform in the pavilion at 6:10 p.m. with a repeat performance at 6:50 p.m., and the Rock Band will perform in the auditorium at 6:30 p.m. with a repeat performance at 7:10 p.m. Come and be a part of this annual tradition!

post_text:
To the JMPS Community:

Mr. Batchelder and Mrs. Curtis have resigned from directing and co-directing/choreographing the all-school musical. If you would like to read Mr. Batchelder's resignation speech from assembly on Monday morning, 9/30/19, please email Mrs. Curtis.

Anyone interested in directing and/or choreographing should contact the JMPS Fine Arts Director, Mrs. Amy Schilling, at Aschilling@madisonprep.org. The new director and choreographer would be subject to JMPS administration approval. A fingerprint clearance card would need to be secured before the first rehearsal. There is a modest stipend attached to these positions. The new director would have the latitude to select the musical, although the musical selection would also be subject to administration approval.
